# Artistic Swimming Training Analysis System — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is an Artistic Swimming (synchronized swimming) training analysis dashboard.
It uses Streamlit + MediaPipe + dual IMU sensors to analyze swimming technique
and provide FINA-standard scoring feedback to coaches and athletes.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.12, Streamlit, Plotly, MediaPipe, NumPy, pandas, scipy
- Testing: pytest (TDD workflow)
- Data format: CSV (IMU sensor data + vision pose data)
- Hardware: M5StickC Plus2 (IMU nodes), DroidCam iOS (camera)

## Development Rules
- Write tests first, then implementation (TDD)
- Run `python -m pytest tests/ -v` after every change to ensure nothing breaks
- Chart builder components are pure functions (no streamlit imports) for testability
- All configurable parameters go in config.toml, never hardcoded
- UI text in Chinese (this is for Chinese coaching teams)
- Update task.md after completing features

## Key Files
- `task.md` — Task tracker, your compass for what to do next
- `config.toml` — FINA thresholds and hardware configuration
- `dashboard/core/scoring.py` — Scoring engine (8 biomechanical metrics)
- `dashboard/core/vision_angles.py` — Vision angle calculations from MediaPipe landmarks
- `dashboard/core/analysis.py` — IMU signal analysis (tilt, smoothing)
- `dashboard/core/data_loader.py` — CSV data loading (dual IMU support)
- `dashboard/pages/training.py` — Main training analysis page (4 tabs)
- `dashboard/components/` — Plotly chart builders (gauge, timeline, waveform)
- `docs/plans/` — Design documents explaining architecture decisions

## Data Formats
- IMU CSV columns: `timestamp_local, timestamp_device, node, state, set, ax, ay, az, gx, gy, gz`
- Vision CSV columns: `timestamp_local, frame, joint, angle_deg, visible, fps`
- Landmarks CSV: `timestamp_local, frame`, then 33 landmarks x 4 columns each (`{name}_x, {name}_y, {name}_z, {name}_vis`)
- Two IMU nodes: NODE_A1 (forearm), NODE_L1 (shin)

## Architecture Patterns
- `dashboard/core/` — Pure Python logic, no UI dependencies
- `dashboard/components/` — Plotly chart builders, return Figure objects
- `dashboard/pages/` — Streamlit page files, compose core + components
- `dashboard/config.py` — Config load/save (toml format)
- Graceful degradation: missing data sources produce partial results, never crash

## Common Tasks for Cursor
- "Add a new chart" → Create in `dashboard/components/`, test in `tests/test_chart_builders.py`, use in `dashboard/pages/`
- "Add a new metric" → Add calculation in `dashboard/core/`, add to scoring engine, add gauge in training page
- "Change FINA thresholds" → Edit `config.toml`, per-metric section under `[fina.metric_name]`
- "Fix a bug" → Reproduce with a test first, then fix

## References
- FINA Artistic Swimming Figures Manual 2022-2025
- MediaPipe Pose Landmarks: 33 points, indices 0-32
- Key landmarks: shoulder(11/12), hip(23/24), knee(25/26), ankle(27/28)
